<headline>Winter Storm Watch issued January 14 at 3:19AM CST until January 16 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY MORNING THROUGH
SATURDAY EVENING...
* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches possible, with locally higher amounts possible in
higher terrain.
* WHERE...Carroll and Madison Counties.
* WHEN...From Saturday morning through Saturday evening.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Locally heavy snowfall will be possible
across parts of northwest Arkansas. Locally higher amounts
closer to 6 inches will be possible, especially for locations
above 1800 feet.</description>
<instruction>Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.</instruction>
